{101}{}{这是一位当地居民，相貌令人反感。对他来说，当地的生活似乎很凄凉。 -- Here is a local resident of a rather repulsive appearance. It seems that local life was bleak for him.}

### {200}{}{What do you want?}
{200}{}{你想要什么？ -- What do you want?}
### {201}{}{I just want to know how life is in this small town.}
{201}{}{我只想知道这个小镇的生活怎么样。 -- I just want to know how life is in this small town.}
### {202}{}{Life is bad. Just like everywhere else nowadays. But we have plenty of clean water. It's already worth it to choose Casa Grande for your stay.}
{202}{}{生活很糟糕。就像现在其他地方一样。但是我们有充足的清洁水。选择格兰德之家住宿已经很值得了。 -- Life is bad. Just like everywhere else nowadays. But we have plenty of clean water. It's already worth it to choose Casa Grande for your stay.}
### {203}{}{Then why are the streets so deserted here?}
{203}{}{那为什么这里的街道如此冷清呢？ -- Then why are the streets so deserted here?}
### {204}{}{I'll tell you what, stranger. Casa Grande has a complicated history. And what we have learned from this story is that it is better not to ask questions about the past. Do you understand me? That's great.}
{204}{}{我告诉你吧，陌生人。格兰德之家有着复杂的历史。我们从这个故事中学到的是，最好不要问关于过去的问题。你明白我的意思吗？太好了。 -- I'll tell you what, stranger. Casa Grande has a complicated history. And what we have learned from this story is that it is better not to ask questions about the past. Do you understand me? That's great.}
### {205}{}{Sounds like you have something to regret.}
{205}{}{听起来你有些后悔。 -- Sounds like you have something to regret.}
### {206}{}{Everyone in this city has had losses. And we are no exception. We lost our old house and our son. Therefore, no one here is going to reveal their soul to the first person they meet.}
{206}{}{这个城市的每个人都遭受了损失。我们也不例外。我们失去了老房子和儿子。因此，这里没有人会向他们遇到的第一个人透露他们的灵魂。 -- Everyone in this city has had losses. And we are no exception. We lost our old house and our son. Therefore, no one here is going to reveal their soul to the first person they meet.}
### {207}{}{Yes, I understand. I hope you'll forgive my curiosity. Goodbye.}
{207}{}{是的，我理解。我希望你能原谅我的好奇心。再见 -- Yes, I understand. I hope you'll forgive my curiosity. Goodbye.}
